        <para>
            <graphic fileref="images/fieldset.1.png" align="center" valign="middle" width="1000px"/>
        </para>
        <para>Instead of, for example, inputting one name in an author field and another name in a translator field, here you choose the "roles" played by each "named entity" with regard to the publication. Most frequently used are author and editor, but it is possible to record many specific roles.</para>
        <para>You can assign various roles to one person or one institution in the same publication: One person may have both edited and translated a certain work. To attribute more than one role to one and the same name, click the <guibutton>+</guibutton> button under the "Role" label.</para>
        <para>In most cases, drop-down lists like those illustrated above have default values, here "author" in role, but you can change this value as you wish.</para>
